result.title: Getting Started
result.content:
• Here is a google drive folder for the material.
  • You will find a warm-up contest to refresh the language you are gonna use and get familiar with the problem format, submission system... etc. Please try to solve them all and get them accepted.
  • When you try to submit, you will be asked for the language of the source code. All supported languages are acceptable, so you are free to write in the language you feel comfortable with. However, I can only support you in java 3shan dy el haga elly fahmha y3ny :"D

Some tips about submissions:

  • Don't include java packages
  • i/o java guide
  • A problem has a time limit which is the time your code takes in the worst case. For example, if 1 <= n <= 100 & 1 <= m <= 30 & complexity is O(n^2 m) then in the worst case, your code will have make 3e5 operations in the worst case. Today's machines make around 1e8 operations in 3 seconds.
